This paper discusses the evolution of radio access technologies for vehicular communications, which falls under the category of networked and distributed systems (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the salient features and mechanisms of these technologies, which involves information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the reliability and security aspects of these technologies, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper discusses the potential impact of these technologies on autonomous driving, which involves artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
